The National Enquirer reports that "American Idol" judge  and reality show veteran  Paula Abdul has signed a deal to produce and star in a new cheerleading reality competition show centered around cheerleading camps. The show will air on Fox, the home of "American Idol." The New York Post points out that her previous attempt at a reality show, "Hey Paula," did not succeed in the ratings. Abdul's fellow judge, Randy Jackson, recently got his own dance reality show, "America's Best Dance Crew," which airs on MTV. Below, watch the trailer to another one of Paula's many projects, her cardio fitness video, "Cardio Cheer." [Source: Huffington Post]